verbose_text: Cao et al suggested that human dermal microvascular endothelial cell-1 in patients with inflammatory skin disease induced chemokines, including CXCL8, CX3CL1 and CXCL16, by activating the NF-kappaB signaling pathway when stimulated by TNF-alpha, which is in agreement with our previous finding that LPS-NF-kappaB-CX3CL1 exists in human bronchial epithelial cells.
